owered Digital Transformation","risk_register":[],"estimated_sprints":6,"features":[],"acceptance_criteria":["[Compliance] Implement risk-based AML/CFT programme","[Compliance] Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers","[Compliance] Register beneficial owners in national registry","[Compliance] File suspicious activity reports (SAR) within 24 hours","[Compliance] Screen customers against UN and national sanctions lists"],"phase":3},{"epic_id":"EPIC-72089199","title":"Manage Official List Operation","subdomain_group":"Manage Regulatory Operation (Day-to-Day)","description":"","business_value":"","strategic_rationale":"Enterprises using AI report 20-30% productivity gains and 15% cost reduction on average","governance_reference":"FATF Recommendations (AML/CFT) — FATF","trend_alignment":"AI-Powered Digital Transformation","risk_register":[],"estimated_sprints":6,"features":[],"acceptance_criteria":["[Compliance] Implement risk-based AML/CFT programme","[Compliance] Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers","[Compliance] Register beneficial owners in national registry","[Compliance] File suspicious activity reports (SAR) within 24 hours","[Compliance] Screen customers against UN and national sanctions lists"],"phase":3},{"epic_id":"EPIC-B0D22E8F","title":"Manage Operation Conduct","subdomain_group":"Manage Regulatory Operation (Day-to-Day)","description":"Capability to govern and execute day-to-day regulatory operations within the Commercial Bank\'s digital financial regulation core, ensuring conduct standards align with FATF AML/CFT obligations. Scope covers regulatory operation execution, monitoring, escalation, and reporting across customer lifecycle and transaction flows.","business_value":"Reduce regulatory breach incidents by 40% through embedded conduct controls, and accelerate SAR filing turnaround to under 24 hours improving regulator trust and avoiding fines.","strategic_rationale":"Per Gartner Top Trends 2025, enterprises adopting AI-powered digital transformation report 20-30% productivity gains and 15% cost reduction — applying agentic AI workflows to regulatory operations enables Commercial Bank to scale conduct oversight without proportional headcount growth.","governance_reference":"FATF Recommendations (AML/CFT) — FATF","trend_alignment":"AI-Powered Digital Transformation","risk_register":["Regulatory interpretation drift between FATF 2023 guidance and local regulator expectations may require rework of risk models mid-delivery","GenAI-drafted SAR narratives may introduce hallucination risk, requiring human-in-the-loop review and slowing the 24-hour filing SLA"],"estimated_sprints":6,"features":[{"title":"AML/CFT Risk-Based Operations Engine","description":"Operationalises a risk-based AML/CFT programme with tiered controls and continuous monitoring across customer and transaction lifecycles.","technical_notes":"Leverages Generative AI for narrative SAR drafting, Agentic workflows for case triage, and Vector databases for typology similarity search.","user_stories":[{"role":"Financial Crime Analyst","want":"an AI-assisted case triage workspace that prioritises alerts by risk score","so_that":"high-risk cases are investigated and reported within regulatory deadlines","acceptance_criteria":["Risk-based AML/CFT programme rules configurable per customer segment","SAR drafts auto-generated and submitted within 24 hours of escalation","Sanctions screening hits routed to L2 review within 15 minutes"],"tasks":[{"title":"Design risk-based scoring model","description":"Define customer and transaction risk factors aligned to FATF Recommendations 2023.","estimated_days":6,"assignee_role":"Solutions Architect"},{"title":"Build GenAI SAR drafting service","description":"Implement generative AI pipeline that drafts SAR narratives from case evidence.","estimated_days":8,"assignee_role":"Data Engineer"},{"title":"Integrate sanctions screening API","description":"Connect UN and national sanctions list providers with real-time screening hooks.","estimated_days":5,"assignee_role":"Security Analyst"}]}],"estimated_story_points":13},{"title":"Enhanced Due Diligence & Beneficial Ownership","description":"Executes EDD workflows for high-risk customers and synchronises beneficial ownership data with the national registry.","technical_notes":"Agentic workflows orchestrate KYC evidence gathering; vector databases support entity resolution against PEP and adverse media corpora.","user_stories":[{"role":"KYC Operations Officer","want":"an EDD workflow that captures beneficial ownership and submits it to the national registry","so_that":"the bank meets transparency obligations and avoids onboarding sanctioned entities","acceptance_criteria":["Enhanced due diligence completed for 100% of high-risk customer segments","Beneficial owner records reconciled to national registry weekly","Adverse media checks logged with auditable evidence trail"],"tasks":[{"title":"Configure EDD agentic workflow","description":"Build agentic orchestration that automates evidence collection for high-risk segments.","estimated_days":7,"assignee_role":"Solutions Architect"},{"title":"Implement registry submission adapter","description":"Develop secure API adapter to register beneficial owners in the national registry.","estimated_days":5,"assignee_role":"Integration Engineer"},{"title":"Deploy entity resolution vector store","description":"Stand up vector database to match counterparties against PEP and adverse media datasets.","estimated_days":6,"assignee_role":"Data Engineer"}]}],"estimated_story_points":8}],"acceptance_criteria":["Implement risk-based AML/CFT programme","Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers","Register beneficial owners in national registry","File suspicious activity reports (SAR) within 24 hours","Screen customers against UN and national sanctions lists","Achieve 95% straight-through processing on regulatory operation tickets within 12-week pilot","Phase exit: independent audit confirms FATF 2023 alignment with zero critical findings"],"phase":3},{"epic_id":"EPIC-3C0D0506","title":"Manage Operation Forms & Templates","subdomain_group":"Manage Regulatory Operation (Day-to-Day)","description":"Establish a centralised, AI-enabled capability for Commercial Bank to author, govern, and distribute regulatory operation forms and templates used in day-to-day digital financial regulation activities. Scope covers form lifecycle management, template versioning, regulatory metadata tagging, and integration with downstream KYC, AML/CFT, and SAR workflows within the Manage Regulatory Operation (Day-to-Day) sub-domain.","business_value":"Reduce manual form preparation effort by 25% across regulatory operations teams and improve first-time-right submission rates to regulators by standardising templates aligned to FATF and national sanctions obligations.","strategic_rationale":"Per Gartner Top Trends 2025 (AI-Powered Digital Transformation), enterprises adopting AI-driven workflows report 20-30% productivity gains and 15% cost reduction — directly applicable to template authoring, regulatory metadata extraction, and form auto-population for Commercial Bank.","governance_reference":"FATF Recommendations (AML/CFT) — FATF","trend_alignment":"AI-Powered Digital Transformation","risk_register":["Regulatory template drift if FATF or national sanctions list updates are not synchronised into the vector database in near real-time","AI-generated clause suggestions may introduce non-compliant language without sufficient human review controls"],"estimated_sprints":6,"features":[{"title":"Regulatory Template Authoring & Versioning","description":"AI-assisted authoring environment for creating, versioning, and approving regulatory forms and templates with embedded compliance metadata.","technical_notes":"Leverages Generative AI for draft template generation, Vector databases for clause retrieval from regulatory corpus, and Agentic workflows for review/approval routing.","user_stories":[{"role":"Regulatory Operations Analyst","want":"to author and version regulatory templates with AI-suggested clauses","so_that":"templates remain aligned to FATF and national regulatory updates without manual rework","acceptance_criteria":["Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers","Template versions are immutable and auditable","AI suggestions cite source regulation with confidence score"],"tasks":[{"title":"Design template metadata schema","description":"Define metadata fields covering regulation reference, jurisdiction, risk tier, and version per FATF Recommendations.","estimated_days":4,"assignee_role":"Solutions Architect"},{"title":"Build GenAI clause suggestion service","description":"Implement RAG pipeline using vector DB indexed on FATF and national regulatory texts to suggest template clauses.","estimated_days":8,"assignee_role":"Data Engineer"},{"title":"Implement version control workflow","description":"Configure agentic approval workflow with maker-checker controls for template publication.","estimated_days":5,"assignee_role":"Solutions Architect"}]}],"estimated_story_points":8},{"title":"Form Distribution & Downstream Integration","description":"Distribute approved templates to KYC, sanctions screening, and SAR workflows with automated population from core banking and customer data sources.","technical_notes":"Agentic workflows orchestrate form rendering and submission; AMD MI300X inference accelerates batch screening enrichment.","user_stories":[{"role":"Compliance Officer","want":"approved templates auto-distributed to operational workflows with pre-populated customer data","so_that":"regulatory submissions are timely, accurate, and traceable","acceptance_criteria":["Register beneficial owners in national registry","File suspicious activity reports (SAR) within 24 hours","Form distribution latency under 5 minutes from publish event"],"tasks":[{"title":"Build template distribution API","description":"Expose REST/event API for downstream regulatory operation systems to consume latest approved templates.","estimated_days":6,"assignee_role":"Integration Engineer"},{"title":"Integrate sanctions screening hook","description":"Connect form submission events to UN and national sanctions list screening service prior to filing.","estimated_days":7,"assignee_role":"Security Analyst"},{"title":"Configure SAR 24-hour SLA monitor","description":"Implement monitoring and alerting to ensure SAR forms are filed within 24 hours of trigger event.","estimated_days":4,"assignee_role":"DevOps Engineer"}]}],"estimated_story_points":13}],"acceptance_criteria":["Implement risk-based AML/CFT programme","Screen customers against UN and national sanctions lists","90% of regulatory forms generated from approved templates with zero critical metadata defects","Phase exit: All templates migrated to versioned repository, signed off by Compliance and Operations, and integrated with SAR workflow","[Compliance] Conduct enhanced due diligence for high-risk customers","[Compliance] Register beneficial owners in national registry","[Compliance] File suspicious activity reports (SAR) within 24 hours"],"phase":3}],"objectives":[],"key_milestones":["Manage Market Intelligence Monitoring","Manage Market Surveillance Monitoring"]}],"compliance_summary":{"score":82,"issues":["No measurable [KPI] acceptance criteria are defined across any epic — performance indicators are absent, so success cannot be quantitatively tracked.","All epics use an identical, copy-pasted set of compliance ACs regardless of epic purpose (e.g., \'Manage Industry Outreach Engagement\' or \'Manage Legislation Draft\' is unlikely to genuinely involve filing SARs or screening customers against sanctions lists), suggesting boilerplate compliance tagging rather than tailored controls.","Phase 1 (\'Foundation & Quick Wins\') includes enforcement and legislation epics that typically depend on legislative planning/drafting capabilities scheduled later in Phase 2 — a dependency inversion (Manage Enforcement Investigation/Complaints precedes Manage Legislation Planning/Draft/Publishing).","Phase 3 \'Manage Market Surveillance Monitoring\' epic appears truncated in the roadmap and may have incomplete acceptance criteria.","Risk factors (operational, data quality, sanctions evasion typologies, PEP risk, jurisdictional risk) are not explicitly addressed at the epic level — only generic FATF controls are listed.","Only one standard (FATF) is referenced; related governance frameworks commonly applicable to enforcement, legislation, and market surveillance (e.g., data protection, records management, ISO 37301 compliance management) are not represented.","No time-bound milestones or delivery dates are attached to phases or epics."],"recommendations":["Add [KPI] acceptance criteria to every epic with measurable, time-bound targets (e.g., \'% SARs filed within 24 hours ≥ 98% by Q2\', \'sanctions screening false-positive rate < 5%\').","Tailor the [Compliance] AC set per epic so that only relevant FATF requirements are claimed (e.g., legislation epics should map to legislative-design controls, not SAR filing).","Reorder the roadmap so Legislation Planning/Drafting/Publishing precedes Enforcement Investigation, Complaints, and Burden management to remove dependency violations.","Complete the truncated Phase 3 \'Manage Market Surveillance Monitoring\' epic with full ACs.","Introduce explicit risk-register linkages in each epic (inherent risk, residual risk, mitigations, owner).","Broaden applicable standards to include data protection (e.g., GDPR/national equivalents), ISO 37301 (Compliance Management), and records-retention obligations relevant to enforcement and legislation workflows.","Attach delivery timelines and exit criteria to each phase to make the roadmap auditable."],"standards_covered":["FATF Recommendations (AML/CFT)"]},"amd_metrics":{"gpu_device":"CPU","rocm_version":null,"processing_time_seconds":0.0,"capabi